This paper primarily focuses on analyzing adversarial attacks against deep learning for intrusion detection in IoT networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also compares the performance of two types of neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses a dataset specific to IoT networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). Finally, the paper uses computer vision techniques to analyze the dataset, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV).
